00:42:09.114 --> 00:42:12.453 align:middle line:90%


00:42:12.453 --> 00:42:17.740 align:middle line:84%
They are the biggest
wounds of humanity.

00:42:17.740 --> 00:42:20.180 align:middle line:84%
Every kind of serving
is a blessing.

00:42:20.180 --> 00:42:25.330 align:middle line:90%


00:42:25.330 --> 00:42:27.670 align:middle line:90%
>> Sir, excuse me.

00:42:27.670 --> 00:42:31.150 align:middle line:84%
So can I go back
to being a doctor?

00:42:31.150 --> 00:42:32.860 align:middle line:90%
>> It's up to you.

00:42:32.860 --> 00:42:36.400 align:middle line:84%
But maybe the terrestrial
doctor is not the same

00:42:36.400 --> 00:42:37.960 align:middle line:90%
as the spiritual doctor.

00:42:37.960 --> 00:42:39.880 align:middle line:90%
>> What can I do?

00:42:39.880 --> 00:42:43.150 align:middle line:84%
>> Know that the
will, persistence,

00:42:43.150 --> 00:42:47.200 align:middle line:84%
and what is worth the
work go along together.

00:42:47.200 --> 00:42:52.450 align:middle line:84%
When the one who serves is
ready, work presents itself.

00:42:52.450 --> 00:42:54.887 align:middle line:90%
Let's find work, my sister.

00:42:54.887 --> 00:42:58.300 align:middle line:90%
[EXHALES]

00:42:58.300 --> 00:43:00.640 align:middle line:84%
>> There is an ocean of
invisible matter around

00:43:00.640 --> 00:43:02.620 align:middle line:90%
the Earth.

00:43:02.620 --> 00:43:06.580 align:middle line:84%
Astral City is at the top of a
chain of spiritual mountains,

00:43:06.580 --> 00:43:09.010 align:middle line:84%
just one among
thousands of cities

00:43:09.010 --> 00:43:11.554 align:middle line:90%
that hover over the planet.

00:43:11.554 --> 00:43:14.506 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:43:14.506 --> 00:43:27.030 align:middle line:90%


00:43:27.030 --> 00:43:28.290 align:middle line:90%
>> Readjustment Chambers.

00:43:28.290 --> 00:43:31.620 align:middle line:90%


00:43:31.620 --> 00:43:33.780 align:middle line:90%
Welcome, my sister.

00:43:33.780 --> 00:43:35.490 align:middle line:90%
Welcome.

00:43:35.490 --> 00:43:37.467 align:middle line:90%
Readjustment Chambers.

00:43:37.467 --> 00:43:39.300 align:middle line:84%
This may not be the
heaven you've dreamt of,

00:43:39.300 --> 00:43:41.370 align:middle line:84%
but we'll take care of
everyone with much love.

00:43:41.370 --> 00:43:43.210 align:middle line:90%
>> Has my niece arrived?

00:43:43.210 --> 00:43:44.010 align:middle line:90%
>> On that one.

00:43:44.010 --> 00:43:46.900 align:middle line:90%


00:43:46.900 --> 00:43:47.890 align:middle line:90%
Readjustment Chambers.

00:43:47.890 --> 00:43:49.528 align:middle line:90%
>> Eloisa.

00:43:49.528 --> 00:43:51.350 align:middle line:90%
[CHATTER]

00:43:51.350 --> 00:43:58.750 align:middle line:90%


00:43:58.750 --> 00:44:03.430 align:middle line:84%
>> I could never have imagined
the potential of our minds.

00:44:03.430 --> 00:44:08.620 align:middle line:84%
Here, many still use their
looks from life on Earth

00:44:08.620 --> 00:44:11.410 align:middle line:84%
but the changes
had to be deeper.

00:44:11.410 --> 00:44:14.350 align:middle line:84%
>> Uncle, I never thought you
would be the one to welcome me

00:44:14.350 --> 00:44:15.910 align:middle line:90%
when I died.

00:44:15.910 --> 00:44:18.770 align:middle line:90%
>> You need to drink Eloisa.

00:44:18.770 --> 00:44:20.740 align:middle line:90%
>> Mom was so sad when you died.

00:44:20.740 --> 00:44:22.480 align:middle line:90%
It was so sudden.

00:44:22.480 --> 00:44:24.160 align:middle line:90%
She always prayed for you.

00:44:24.160 --> 00:44:26.860 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah, I know.

00:44:26.860 --> 00:44:28.660 align:middle line:90%
>> How do you know?

00:44:28.660 --> 00:44:32.866 align:middle line:90%
[COUGHING, GASPING]

00:44:32.866 --> 00:44:34.600 align:middle line:84%
>> The first hours
are the worst.

00:44:34.600 --> 00:44:36.880 align:middle line:90%
Soon the pain will go away.

00:44:36.880 --> 00:44:38.260 align:middle line:90%
You've suffered enough.

00:44:38.260 --> 00:44:41.290 align:middle line:90%
>> Lucius, what happened to her?

00:44:41.290 --> 00:44:43.420 align:middle line:90%
>> I don't need your pity.

00:44:43.420 --> 00:44:45.940 align:middle line:84%
>> We'll take care
of you, Eloisa.

00:44:45.940 --> 00:44:48.310 align:middle line:84%
>> I don't need to
be taken care of.

00:44:48.310 --> 00:44:51.250 align:middle line:90%
>> Uncle, help me go back.

00:44:51.250 --> 00:44:53.360 align:middle line:84%
My fiance must be
waiting for me.

00:44:53.360 --> 00:44:57.023 align:middle line:84%
>> Eloisa, I'll take
you to our home here.

00:44:57.023 --> 00:44:58.690 align:middle line:84%
Your grandmother,
Laura, and your aunts,

00:44:58.690 --> 00:44:59.785 align:middle line:90%
Judite and Iolanda--

00:44:59.785 --> 00:45:00.100 align:middle line:90%
>> Uncle--

00:45:00.100 --> 00:45:01.000 align:middle line:90%
>> --await you.

00:45:01.000 --> 00:45:02.333 align:middle line:90%
>> --I don't have any home here.

00:45:02.333 --> 00:45:04.150 align:middle line:90%
You know this.

00:45:04.150 --> 00:45:06.320 align:middle line:90%
Uncle, send me back, please.

00:45:06.320 --> 00:45:07.720 align:middle line:90%
>> Easy.

00:45:07.720 --> 00:45:08.785 align:middle line:90%
Eloisa, rest.

00:45:08.785 --> 00:45:14.230 align:middle line:90%


00:45:14.230 --> 00:45:15.610 align:middle line:90%
I'll prepare your departure.

00:45:15.610 --> 00:45:20.500 align:middle line:90%


00:45:20.500 --> 00:45:21.300 align:middle line:90%
Andre?

00:45:21.300 --> 00:45:23.200 align:middle line:90%
Andre?

00:45:23.200 --> 00:45:24.430 align:middle line:90%
You should observe.

00:45:24.430 --> 00:45:26.245 align:middle line:90%
You have a lot to learn here.

00:45:26.245 --> 00:45:27.880 align:middle line:90%
>> Thank you, Lucius.

00:45:27.880 --> 00:45:29.070 align:middle line:90%
[CHATTER]

00:45:29.070 --> 00:45:35.740 align:middle line:90%


00:45:35.740 --> 00:45:38.260 align:middle line:84%
>> Don't tell me
I have to relax.

00:45:38.260 --> 00:45:40.180 align:middle line:90%
>> How do you feel?

00:45:40.180 --> 00:45:42.010 align:middle line:84%
>> Alive and dead
at the same time.

00:45:42.010 --> 00:45:44.641 align:middle line:84%
>> You know, I couldn't
define it better myself.

00:45:44.641 --> 00:45:48.880 align:middle line:90%
[COUGHING, GASPS]

00:45:48.880 --> 00:45:50.000 align:middle line:90%
>> Who are you?

00:45:50.000 --> 00:45:50.800 align:middle line:90%
>> I am a doctor.

00:45:50.800 --> 00:45:52.510 align:middle line:90%
I'm Doctor Andre Luiz.

00:45:52.510 --> 00:45:53.960 align:middle line:90%
>> So explain it to me.

00:45:53.960 --> 00:45:56.170 align:middle line:84%
Why do I still feel
so much as pain?

00:45:56.170 --> 00:45:59.080 align:middle line:90%
>> Can you get up, please?

00:45:59.080 --> 00:46:00.340 align:middle line:90%
If I may examine you?

00:46:00.340 --> 00:46:01.258 align:middle line:90%
Yes, yes.

00:46:01.258 --> 00:46:03.550 align:middle line:84%
>> I wonder if I won't stop
suffering even after death.

00:46:03.550 --> 00:46:04.390 align:middle line:90%
>> Take a breath.

00:46:04.390 --> 00:46:05.320 align:middle line:90%
That's it.

00:46:05.320 --> 00:46:07.540 align:middle line:90%
Does it hurt?

00:46:07.540 --> 00:46:09.220 align:middle line:90%
And here?

00:46:09.220 --> 00:46:11.440 align:middle line:90%
That's it, breathe, breathe.

00:46:11.440 --> 00:46:12.700 align:middle line:90%
[GASPING AIR]

00:46:12.700 --> 00:46:14.600 align:middle line:90%
>> Easy, God.

00:46:14.600 --> 00:46:15.823 align:middle line:90%
Easy, easy.

00:46:15.823 --> 00:46:17.240 align:middle line:84%
>> Take your hands
off her please.

00:46:17.240 --> 00:46:18.657 align:middle line:84%
>> But she needs
help immediately.

00:46:18.657 --> 00:46:20.710 align:middle line:90%
>> Leave it to me.

00:46:20.710 --> 00:46:22.735 align:middle line:90%
Thank you.

00:46:22.735 --> 00:46:24.220 align:middle line:90%
[GASPING]

00:46:24.220 --> 00:46:27.840 align:middle line:90%
>> But what would have happened?

00:46:27.840 --> 00:46:28.980 align:middle line:90%
What did I do to her?

00:46:28.980 --> 00:46:29.780 align:middle line:90%
What?

00:46:29.780 --> 00:46:31.620 align:middle line:90%
Was she having a crisis?

00:46:31.620 --> 00:46:36.900 align:middle line:84%
>> Yes, something like it,
but you could say that.

00:46:36.900 --> 00:46:38.260 align:middle line:90%
>> I know.

00:46:38.260 --> 00:46:39.060 align:middle line:90%
I'm sorry.

00:46:39.060 --> 00:46:41.070 align:middle line:90%
I'm a doctor.

00:46:41.070 --> 00:46:43.170 align:middle line:90%
>> Earth diplomas.

00:46:43.170 --> 00:46:44.790 align:middle line:90%
>> But what would have happened?

00:46:44.790 --> 00:46:46.920 align:middle line:84%
If she's already
dead, then why--

00:46:46.920 --> 00:46:48.360 align:middle line:90%
>> You were researching?

00:46:48.360 --> 00:46:50.610 align:middle line:84%
>> --no, I'm trying
to learn and help too.

00:46:50.610 --> 00:46:51.870 align:middle line:90%
>> Help?

00:46:51.870 --> 00:46:54.450 align:middle line:90%
>> Of course, I need to work.

00:46:54.450 --> 00:46:55.890 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah, and why is that?

00:46:55.890 --> 00:46:57.570 align:middle line:84%
>> I want to visit
my family on Earth.

00:46:57.570 --> 00:47:00.000 align:middle line:90%
I need to earn it.

00:47:00.000 --> 00:47:02.160 align:middle line:90%
>> You want to earn it?

00:47:02.160 --> 00:47:04.753 align:middle line:84%
>> Yes, isn't that how
things work around here?

00:47:04.753 --> 00:47:05.670 align:middle line:90%
>> You really want it?

00:47:05.670 --> 00:47:06.840 align:middle line:90%
>> I want to earn it.

00:47:06.840 --> 00:47:08.280 align:middle line:90%
>> Then come, come.

00:47:08.280 --> 00:47:09.720 align:middle line:90%
Our brother needs cleaning.

00:47:09.720 --> 00:47:11.100 align:middle line:90%
You can start here.

00:47:11.100 --> 00:47:13.140 align:middle line:90%
>> But this is a job for nurses.

00:47:13.140 --> 00:47:14.460 align:middle line:90%
>> Do you want it or not?

00:47:14.460 --> 00:47:17.130 align:middle line:84%
>> But you could use me
in so many other jobs.

00:47:17.130 --> 00:47:18.847 align:middle line:90%
I've studied so hard in life.

00:47:18.847 --> 00:47:21.180 align:middle line:84%
>> What do you know about
spiritual medicine, my friend?

00:47:21.180 --> 00:47:24.760 align:middle line:84%
>> I know nothing about
it, but I want to learn.

00:47:24.760 --> 00:47:28.260 align:middle line:84%
It's just that there are so
many laws here or new ways

00:47:28.260 --> 00:47:29.595 align:middle line:90%
of applying old laws.

00:47:29.595 --> 00:47:33.270 align:middle line:84%
>> No, the laws are the same,
but they are done individually.

00:47:33.270 --> 00:47:36.380 align:middle line:90%
>> Oh, what is happening to me?

00:47:36.380 --> 00:47:37.700 align:middle line:90%
[GASPS]

00:47:37.700 --> 00:47:38.676 align:middle line:90%


00:47:38.676 --> 00:47:40.628 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:47:40.628 --> 00:47:45.030 align:middle line:90%


00:47:45.030 --> 00:47:48.930 align:middle line:84%
>> Have you recharged
your strengths?

00:47:48.930 --> 00:47:55.920 align:middle line:84%
>> My dearest daughter,
wherever you may be,

00:47:55.920 --> 00:47:58.410 align:middle line:90%
I want to love you forever.

00:47:58.410 --> 00:48:05.160 align:middle line:84%
From the very bottom of my
heart, I wish you peace.

00:48:05.160 --> 00:48:06.810 align:middle line:90%
Godspeed, my dear.

00:48:06.810 --> 00:48:14.360 align:middle line:90%


00:48:14.360 --> 00:48:17.420 align:middle line:84%
>> That was a beautiful
prayer from your mom.

00:48:17.420 --> 00:48:19.430 align:middle line:90%
>> And my fiancee?

00:48:19.430 --> 00:48:21.290 align:middle line:90%
Didn't he pray for me?

00:48:21.290 --> 00:48:24.140 align:middle line:90%
>> Doesn't he know life goes on?

00:48:24.140 --> 00:48:26.786 align:middle line:84%
>> We have never
even talked about it.

00:48:26.786 --> 00:48:29.690 align:middle line:90%
[SIGHS]

00:48:29.690 --> 00:48:32.000 align:middle line:84%
>> This shouldn't
have happened to me.

00:48:32.000 --> 00:48:34.220 align:middle line:84%
We're in love and we were
supposed to get married.

00:48:34.220 --> 00:48:36.905 align:middle line:84%
>> Why does your arrival here
mean your love has to end?

00:48:36.905 --> 00:48:40.080 align:middle line:90%


00:48:40.080 --> 00:48:41.190 align:middle line:90%
>> When can I get out?

00:48:41.190 --> 00:48:43.020 align:middle line:84%
>> Once your uncle
comes and gets you.

00:48:43.020 --> 00:48:46.290 align:middle line:84%
>> Now rest and try not to
think about anything, hmm.

00:48:46.290 --> 00:48:52.160 align:middle line:90%


00:48:52.160 --> 00:48:54.040 align:middle line:90%
So my friend, how are you?

00:48:54.040 --> 00:48:55.780 align:middle line:90%
>> I owe you an apology.

00:48:55.780 --> 00:48:59.170 align:middle line:84%
>> No, you only owe an apology
to people who get offended,

00:48:59.170 --> 00:49:00.440 align:middle line:90%
which is not my case.

00:49:00.440 --> 00:49:02.050 align:middle line:84%
>> I didn't mean
to harm her at all.

00:49:02.050 --> 00:49:04.270 align:middle line:84%
>> Do patients take
care of patients?

00:49:04.270 --> 00:49:08.620 align:middle line:84%
>> You were passing to her
fluids from your fragile mind.

00:49:08.620 --> 00:49:10.510 align:middle line:90%
>> But I'm not suicidal.

00:49:10.510 --> 00:49:13.810 align:middle line:84%
>> That's not what
we're talking about.

00:49:13.810 --> 00:49:15.640 align:middle line:90%
>> I'm sorry.

00:49:15.640 --> 00:49:19.750 align:middle line:84%
>> Andre, you're not ready
yet, but you will be.

00:49:19.750 --> 00:49:23.440 align:middle line:84%
Tobias, show our friend to
the exit from the chambers.

00:49:23.440 --> 00:49:55.040 align:middle line:84%
[MUSIC - Beethoven,
"Moonlight Sonata"]

00:49:55.040 --> 00:49:59.060 align:middle line:84%
>> When he was born, you
dedicated yourself to raising

00:49:59.060 --> 00:49:59.930 align:middle line:90%
a good man.

00:49:59.930 --> 00:50:03.260 align:middle line:84%
And when he died, your
dedication grew even more.

00:50:03.260 --> 00:50:05.662 align:middle line:84%
>> It's not an easy
task, Clarencio.

00:50:05.662 --> 00:50:06.620 align:middle line:90%
You were there with us.

00:50:06.620 --> 00:50:08.480 align:middle line:90%
You know that.

00:50:08.480 --> 00:50:10.550 align:middle line:84%
>> Yes, but you're
doing your best.

00:50:10.550 --> 00:50:13.520 align:middle line:90%
And I know you will keep at it.

00:50:13.520 --> 00:50:16.820 align:middle line:84%
>> It took time for me to
accept the fate that he created

00:50:16.820 --> 00:50:18.230 align:middle line:90%
himself.

00:50:18.230 --> 00:50:22.070 align:middle line:84%
>> It's hard to see
brothers stumbling.

00:50:22.070 --> 00:50:23.495 align:middle line:90%
Welcome to Astral City, Luisa.

00:50:23.495 --> 00:50:26.090 align:middle line:90%


00:50:26.090 --> 00:50:29.150 align:middle line:90%
>> I'm glad he's here.

00:50:29.150 --> 00:50:34.727 align:middle line:84%
>> Soon, I believe you
will be allowed to talk

00:50:34.727 --> 00:50:36.723 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:50:36.723 --> 00:52:09.640 align:middle line:90%


00:52:09.640 --> 00:52:13.240 align:middle line:84%
>> Andre, you can't tell
people that you are alive.

00:52:13.240 --> 00:52:16.330 align:middle line:90%
It's just not worth it.

00:52:16.330 --> 00:52:19.570 align:middle line:84%
To know the truth, all
beings need some spirituality

00:52:19.570 --> 00:52:21.550 align:middle line:90%
whatever that it is.

00:52:21.550 --> 00:52:23.125 align:middle line:84%
>> Emmanuel, I don't
have your faith.

00:52:23.125 --> 00:52:25.730 align:middle line:90%


00:52:25.730 --> 00:52:29.120 align:middle line:84%
>> And did you earn the
permission to send the message?

00:52:29.120 --> 00:52:30.710 align:middle line:90%
>> Not yet, no.

00:52:30.710 --> 00:52:32.300 align:middle line:90%
>> Andre, let's do something.

00:52:32.300 --> 00:52:33.630 align:middle line:90%
Let's go in there.

00:52:33.630 --> 00:52:35.840 align:middle line:84%
And you can talk
to the Governor.

00:52:35.840 --> 00:52:37.490 align:middle line:90%
>> And will he see me?

00:52:37.490 --> 00:52:40.891 align:middle line:84%
>> Here, the directors
give the instructions.

00:52:40.891 --> 00:52:43.346 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:52:43.346 --> 00:53:06.960 align:middle line:90%


00:53:06.960 --> 00:53:08.565 align:middle line:90%
>> Welcome, Andre Luiz.

00:53:08.565 --> 00:53:18.085 align:middle line:90%


00:53:18.085 --> 00:53:21.220 align:middle line:84%
In my father's home,
there are many homes.

00:53:21.220 --> 00:53:24.610 align:middle line:84%
I wouldn't trade our
beautiful blue planet

00:53:24.610 --> 00:53:27.190 align:middle line:84%
to live anywhere
else in this galaxy,

00:53:27.190 --> 00:53:31.430 align:middle line:90%
not even in the happy worlds.

00:53:31.430 --> 00:53:33.490 align:middle line:90%
Thank you, Andre.

00:53:33.490 --> 00:53:35.210 align:middle line:90%
Thank you for coming to see me.

00:53:35.210 --> 00:53:39.300 align:middle line:84%
>> Sir, I came to beg
for your permission.

00:53:39.300 --> 00:53:40.930 align:middle line:90%
>> Beg, Andre?

00:53:40.930 --> 00:53:42.607 align:middle line:90%
>> I need to see them.

00:53:42.607 --> 00:53:43.770 align:middle line:90%
[SIGHS]

00:53:43.770 --> 00:53:50.090 align:middle line:90%
>> Family-- Andre, family--

00:53:50.090 --> 00:53:53.240 align:middle line:90%
see, this is my family.

00:53:53.240 --> 00:53:57.510 align:middle line:84%
Beyond the walls, in the
valleys of suffering,

00:53:57.510 --> 00:53:59.930 align:middle line:90%
they are my family too.

00:53:59.930 --> 00:54:02.870 align:middle line:90%
I need to see them too.

00:54:02.870 --> 00:54:05.120 align:middle line:84%
But this is not what
makes you suffer

00:54:05.120 --> 00:54:08.460 align:middle line:84%
the most when you had found you
were speaking with your heart.

00:54:08.460 --> 00:54:13.600 align:middle line:84%
And when the heart
speaks, God speaks for us.

00:54:13.600 --> 00:54:16.795 align:middle line:90%
Regret, unconscious, my brother.

00:54:16.795 --> 00:54:19.760 align:middle line:90%


00:54:19.760 --> 00:54:22.880 align:middle line:90%
>> Forgive me.

00:54:22.880 --> 00:54:25.960 align:middle line:90%
I threw my life away.

00:54:25.960 --> 00:54:29.075 align:middle line:84%
>> There are hearts
that pray for you.

00:54:29.075 --> 00:54:29.875 align:middle line:90%
>> What hearts?

00:54:29.875 --> 00:54:36.435 align:middle line:90%


00:54:36.435 --> 00:54:38.375 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:54:38.375 --> 00:54:45.880 align:middle line:90%


00:54:45.880 --> 00:54:46.680 align:middle line:90%
>> Mom?

00:54:46.680 --> 00:54:47.590 align:middle line:90%
>> My son.

00:54:47.590 --> 00:54:53.000 align:middle line:90%


00:54:53.000 --> 00:54:54.972 align:middle line:90%
[SOBBING]

00:54:54.972 --> 00:55:24.100 align:middle line:90%


00:55:24.100 --> 00:55:26.290 align:middle line:84%
>> Why didn't dad
come to see me?

00:55:26.290 --> 00:55:28.660 align:middle line:84%
>> Your dad is in the
underground regions.

00:55:28.660 --> 00:55:30.430 align:middle line:90%
>> But what did he do?

00:55:30.430 --> 00:55:33.925 align:middle line:10%
>> I have no right to
enumerate your father's deeds.

00:55:33.925 --> 00:55:37.480 align:middle line:84%
But he's already having
the harvest, unfortunately.

00:55:37.480 --> 00:55:38.750 align:middle line:90%
>> And I can't--

00:55:38.750 --> 00:55:40.930 align:middle line:90%
>> No, not a chance for now.

00:55:40.930 --> 00:55:42.220 align:middle line:90%
>> --and you?

00:55:42.220 --> 00:55:46.450 align:middle line:84%
>> I've been close at
a certain distance.

00:55:46.450 --> 00:55:50.590 align:middle line:84%
I've been thinking, what if
we lived a new experience

00:55:50.590 --> 00:55:52.330 align:middle line:90%
in the flesh?

00:55:52.330 --> 00:55:55.750 align:middle line:84%
>> Everything loses its meaning
once we wake up after we die.

00:55:55.750 --> 00:55:57.880 align:middle line:84%
>> Everything
makes sense, Andre.

00:55:57.880 --> 00:55:58.970 align:middle line:90%
>> I don't blame myself.

00:55:58.970 --> 00:56:00.730 align:middle line:90%
I can't absolve myself though.

00:56:00.730 --> 00:56:03.040 align:middle line:90%
Do you have access to Earth?

00:56:03.040 --> 00:56:05.880 align:middle line:84%
>> But do not ask me about
Zelia or the children.

00:56:05.880 --> 00:56:07.210 align:middle line:90%
>> My wife, my children--

00:56:07.210 --> 00:56:09.280 align:middle line:90%
>> You're still a patient.

00:56:09.280 --> 00:56:11.410 align:middle line:84%
>> They just won't
let me work here.

00:56:11.410 --> 00:56:15.640 align:middle line:90%
>> Here, free will is a law too.

00:56:15.640 --> 00:56:17.440 align:middle line:90%
You're a doctor.

00:56:17.440 --> 00:56:21.250 align:middle line:84%
But before that,
you're a good man.

00:56:21.250 --> 00:56:24.010 align:middle line:10%
I'm glad that you're
finding yourself again.

00:56:24.010 --> 00:56:28.210 align:middle line:90%


00:56:28.210 --> 00:56:30.610 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:56:30.610 --> 00:56:33.490 align:middle line:90%


00:56:33.490 --> 00:56:38.915 align:middle line:84%
>> Andre, do you want to roam as
a free spirit or wait for time

00:56:38.915 --> 00:56:39.715 align:middle line:90%
to pass?

00:56:39.715 --> 00:56:46.100 align:middle line:90%


00:56:46.100 --> 00:56:52.694 align:middle line:84%
My son, if you need, I'll
come to you, just think.

00:56:52.694 --> 00:56:55.154 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:56:55.154 --> 00:57:02.042 align:middle line:90%


00:57:02.042 --> 00:57:04.010 align:middle line:90%
[SOBBING]

00:57:04.010 --> 00:57:22.214 align:middle line:90%


00:57:22.214 --> 00:57:23.560 align:middle line:90%
[COUGHING]

00:57:23.560 --> 00:57:24.160 align:middle line:90%


00:57:24.160 --> 00:57:24.960 align:middle line:90%
[CHATTER]

00:57:24.960 --> 00:57:41.440 align:middle line:90%


00:57:41.440 --> 00:57:42.910 align:middle line:90%
>> No, I don't want to.

00:57:42.910 --> 00:57:45.820 align:middle line:90%
>> Easy sister, easy.

00:57:45.820 --> 00:57:47.210 align:middle line:90%
You'll get better.

00:57:47.210 --> 00:57:50.170 align:middle line:90%
You'll get better, easy, easy.

00:57:50.170 --> 00:57:53.200 align:middle line:90%
>> What's happening?

00:57:53.200 --> 00:57:54.730 align:middle line:90%
>> Lie down here brother, easy.

00:57:54.730 --> 00:57:57.050 align:middle line:90%
You're getting cleaned.

00:57:57.050 --> 00:57:58.630 align:middle line:90%
>> Tobias, what's going on?

00:57:58.630 --> 00:58:01.360 align:middle line:90%
>> This is the work, Andre.

00:58:01.360 --> 00:58:02.720 align:middle line:90%
>> I'll be right back.

00:58:02.720 --> 00:58:03.650 align:middle line:90%
[MOANING]

00:58:03.650 --> 00:58:04.450 align:middle line:90%
>> No.

00:58:04.450 --> 00:58:08.950 align:middle line:90%
>> Tobias, a moment please.

00:58:08.950 --> 00:58:11.170 align:middle line:84%
I need you to summon more
servers for the shift,

00:58:11.170 --> 00:58:12.380 align:middle line:90%
otherwise we won't make it.

00:58:12.380 --> 00:58:13.180 align:middle line:90%
Go.

00:58:13.180 --> 00:58:15.670 align:middle line:90%


00:58:15.670 --> 00:58:17.662 align:middle line:90%
[COUGHING]

00:58:17.662 --> 00:58:20.650 align:middle line:90%
[GROANING]

00:58:20.650 --> 00:58:29.610 align:middle line:90%


00:58:29.610 --> 00:58:32.010 align:middle line:90%
>> Stay calm.

00:58:32.010 --> 00:58:35.076 align:middle line:90%
You'll get help, easy.

00:58:35.076 --> 00:58:35.876 align:middle line:90%
That's it.

00:58:35.876 --> 00:58:38.640 align:middle line:90%


00:58:38.640 --> 00:58:39.750 align:middle line:90%
You can rest.

00:58:39.750 --> 00:58:41.730 align:middle line:90%
Many people here will help you.

00:58:41.730 --> 00:58:44.040 align:middle line:84%
You're protected,
safe and protected.

00:58:44.040 --> 00:58:45.852 align:middle line:90%
[EXHALES]

00:58:45.852 --> 00:58:52.080 align:middle line:90%


00:58:52.080 --> 00:58:52.880 align:middle line:90%
Trust me.

00:58:52.880 --> 00:58:55.970 align:middle line:90%
It'll be all right.

00:58:55.970 --> 00:58:57.050 align:middle line:90%
Yes, all right.

00:58:57.050 --> 00:59:03.190 align:middle line:90%


00:59:03.190 --> 00:59:04.798 align:middle line:90%
[HEAVY PANTING]

00:59:04.798 --> 00:59:10.900 align:middle line:90%


00:59:10.900 --> 00:59:12.310 align:middle line:90%
[CHATTER]

00:59:12.310 --> 00:59:29.010 align:middle line:90%


00:59:29.010 --> 00:59:30.570 align:middle line:90%
>> Nurse Narcisa, hi.

00:59:30.570 --> 00:59:34.200 align:middle line:84%
>> You earned double
bonuses for your work.

00:59:34.200 --> 00:59:38.610 align:middle line:84%
Now Andre Luiz, you're a member
of the Readjustment Chambers.

00:59:38.610 --> 00:59:44.080 align:middle line:84%
And as any good server, you
know when it's time to rest.

00:59:44.080 --> 00:59:47.560 align:middle line:84%
>> Thank you, nurse
Narcisa, but I have to work.

00:59:47.560 --> 00:59:50.770 align:middle line:84%
>> No, now it's
time to stop, OK?

00:59:50.770 --> 00:59:53.290 align:middle line:84%
The quality of work
is what's important.

00:59:53.290 --> 00:59:54.310 align:middle line:90%
Do not hurry.

00:59:54.310 --> 01:00:06.950 align:middle line:90%


01:00:06.950 --> 01:00:08.180 align:middle line:90%
>> Lucius, I have a concern.

01:00:08.180 --> 01:00:09.537 align:middle line:90%
Where will I live?

01:00:09.537 --> 01:00:10.370 align:middle line:90%
>> What do you mean?

01:00:10.370 --> 01:00:11.930 align:middle line:90%
You've only started working.

01:00:11.930 --> 01:00:15.230 align:middle line:84%
>> But I didn't know I was going
to leave the hospital for that.

01:00:15.230 --> 01:00:20.150 align:middle line:84%
>> Andre, some time ago, I'd
think this is a complaint--

01:00:20.150 --> 01:00:21.626 align:middle line:90%
that you needed water.

01:00:21.626 --> 01:00:23.760 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHS]

01:00:23.760 --> 01:00:25.630 align:middle line:84%
>> I cannot contain
my curiosity.

01:00:25.630 --> 01:00:28.295 align:middle line:90%
>> Mm-hmm.

01:00:28.295 --> 01:00:31.460 align:middle line:84%
I'm sorry, were you a
doctor or a journalist?

01:00:31.460 --> 01:00:34.310 align:middle line:90%


01:00:34.310 --> 01:00:36.320 align:middle line:90%
>> How many people live here?

01:00:36.320 --> 01:00:37.550 align:middle line:90%
>> Around one million--

01:00:37.550 --> 01:00:38.790 align:middle line:90%
coming and going.

01:00:38.790 --> 01:00:40.850 align:middle line:90%
>> What do I do to buy a house?

01:00:40.850 --> 01:00:42.290 align:middle line:90%
>> Buy, Andre?

01:00:42.290 --> 01:00:44.840 align:middle line:90%
This is not Earth, my friend.

01:00:44.840 --> 01:00:46.370 align:middle line:90%
You can't just accumulate.

01:00:46.370 --> 01:00:48.560 align:middle line:90%
You have to earn it, remember?

01:00:48.560 --> 01:00:50.210 align:middle line:90%
Do not worry about this now.

01:00:50.210 --> 01:00:51.890 align:middle line:90%
Let's enjoy dinner.

01:00:51.890 --> 01:00:54.650 align:middle line:84%
>> I was at the hospital so long
that I don't even remember what

01:00:54.650 --> 01:00:56.195 align:middle line:90%
a good meal tastes like.

01:00:56.195 --> 01:00:57.410 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHTER]

01:00:57.410 --> 01:00:58.850 align:middle line:90%
>> You won't even believe it.

01:00:58.850 --> 01:01:05.600 align:middle line:90%


01:01:05.600 --> 01:01:10.670 align:middle line:84%
>> Flowers from Veneranda,
our beloved minister.

01:01:10.670 --> 01:01:12.450 align:middle line:84%
>> Miss Laura,
you are very kind.

01:01:12.450 --> 01:01:14.907 align:middle line:84%
And I want to thank you for
the invitation made by Lucius.

01:01:14.907 --> 01:01:15.740 align:middle line:90%
>> Don't mention it.

01:01:15.740 --> 01:01:18.000 align:middle line:84%
>> Andre, this home was
earned by all of us,

01:01:18.000 --> 01:01:20.340 align:middle line:84%
especially by my husband
who is already on Earth.

01:01:20.340 --> 01:01:21.140 align:middle line:90%
>> That's right.

01:01:21.140 --> 01:01:22.550 align:middle line:90%
I forgot to tell you, Andre.

01:01:22.550 --> 01:01:26.850 align:middle line:84%
It took my father only 18
years to get this house.

01:01:26.850 --> 01:01:31.000 align:middle line:84%
When you get yours, I'll
probably be reborn already.

01:01:31.000 --> 01:01:33.580 align:middle line:84%
>> Lucius, now that he's
out of the hospital,

01:01:33.580 --> 01:01:35.673 align:middle line:84%
Andrea is worried about
his own situation.

01:01:35.673 --> 01:01:37.840 align:middle line:84%
>> I don't want to bother
you with this, Miss Laura.

01:01:37.840 --> 01:01:39.910 align:middle line:84%
>> There's room for one
more in our home, Andre.

01:01:39.910 --> 01:01:42.940 align:middle line:84%
>> I swore to never cook
again after I passed.

01:01:42.940 --> 01:01:44.170 align:middle line:90%
But what can I do?

01:01:44.170 --> 01:01:44.970 align:middle line:90%
I love it.

01:01:44.970 --> 01:01:45.770 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHS]

01:01:45.770 --> 01:01:46.750 align:middle line:90%
>> Attention, Andre.

01:01:46.750 --> 01:01:48.640 align:middle line:90%
I have a special menu for you.

01:01:48.640 --> 01:01:49.930 align:middle line:10%
Today, we'll have soup.

01:01:49.930 --> 01:01:51.550 align:middle line:90%
>> I made it with love.

01:01:51.550 --> 01:01:54.830 align:middle line:90%
>> It's served with water.

01:01:54.830 --> 01:01:59.560 align:middle line:84%
>> Eloisa, my granddaughter,
you should re-energize too.

01:01:59.560 --> 01:02:01.480 align:middle line:84%
>> Why are you playing
the happy family?

01:02:01.480 --> 01:02:17.970 align:middle line:90%


01:02:17.970 --> 01:02:19.710 align:middle line:90%
>> I'm glad you liked it.

01:02:19.710 --> 01:02:22.400 align:middle line:90%
>> Thank you.

01:02:22.400 --> 01:02:24.880 align:middle line:84%
>> I can't wait
to know our date.

01:02:24.880 --> 01:02:27.040 align:middle line:90%
>> I'm sure we can be farmers.

01:02:27.040 --> 01:02:30.340 align:middle line:84%
And we'll live on
a beautiful farm.

01:02:30.340 --> 01:02:33.400 align:middle line:84%
>> Honey, you know
I'm a man of the city.

01:02:33.400 --> 01:02:35.440 align:middle line:84%
>> Watching you guys
plan your reincarnation,

01:02:35.440 --> 01:02:37.420 align:middle line:90%
it almost seems easy.

01:02:37.420 --> 01:02:40.870 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, I'm sure we can
do it this time around.

01:02:40.870 --> 01:02:42.580 align:middle line:90%
>> We have failed many times.

01:02:42.580 --> 01:02:43.870 align:middle line:90%
What makes you so sure?

01:02:43.870 --> 01:02:47.410 align:middle line:84%
>> The process of reincarnation
is not so easy you know, Andre.

01:02:47.410 --> 01:02:50.990 align:middle line:90%
A detailed plan is needed to--

01:02:50.990 --> 01:02:51.790 align:middle line:90%
Andre Luiz?

01:02:51.790 --> 01:02:54.520 align:middle line:90%


01:02:54.520 --> 01:02:56.110 align:middle line:90%
>> Miss Laura, I'm sorry.

01:02:56.110 --> 01:02:57.250 align:middle line:90%
Will you excuse me?

01:02:57.250 --> 01:02:59.880 align:middle line:90%
>> Of course.

01:02:59.880 --> 01:03:03.010 align:middle line:84%
>> The Minister
will see us soon.

01:03:03.010 --> 01:03:05.290 align:middle line:90%
I can't wait.

01:03:05.290 --> 01:03:09.700 align:middle line:84%
>> Eloisa, have you ever
imagined a life after a life?

01:03:09.700 --> 01:03:12.070 align:middle line:84%
>> Do you know how
we can go back?

01:03:12.070 --> 01:03:14.350 align:middle line:84%
I want to know how
my fiance is doing.

01:03:14.350 --> 01:03:15.430 align:middle line:90%
>> Unfortunately, no.

01:03:15.430 --> 01:03:18.150 align:middle line:90%
>> I need to go.

01:03:18.150 --> 01:03:19.800 align:middle line:84%
>> There are worse
cases than yours.

01:03:19.800 --> 01:03:22.620 align:middle line:84%
Why don't you simply
focus on your recovery?

01:03:22.620 --> 01:03:24.640 align:middle line:84%
>> I'm not worried
about the others.

01:03:24.640 --> 01:03:27.690 align:middle line:84%
And I'm not worried
about my recovery.

01:03:27.690 --> 01:03:28.620 align:middle line:90%
I'm already dead.

01:03:28.620 --> 01:03:29.900 align:middle line:90%
Don't you get it?

01:03:29.900 --> 01:03:30.900 align:middle line:90%
>> You have a privilege.

01:03:30.900 --> 01:03:32.970 align:middle line:90%
>> No compliments, please.

01:03:32.970 --> 01:03:37.150 align:middle line:84%
>> I, for one, never received
those prayers from my relatives

01:03:37.150 --> 01:03:37.950 align:middle line:90%
on Earth.

01:03:37.950 --> 01:03:40.505 align:middle line:90%
>> Well, maybe no one liked you.

01:03:40.505 --> 01:03:42.445 align:middle line:90%
[MELANCHOLY MUSIC]

01:03:42.445 --> 01:03:56.040 align:middle line:90%


01:03:56.040 --> 01:03:58.390 align:middle line:90%
>> Wow, it took me a while.

01:03:58.390 --> 01:04:00.510 align:middle line:90%
It's been a long time, right?

01:04:00.510 --> 01:04:02.640 align:middle line:90%
There are only two files.

01:04:02.640 --> 01:04:03.570 align:middle line:90%
>> What do you mean?

01:04:03.570 --> 01:04:05.845 align:middle line:90%
>> The record of two people.

01:04:05.845 --> 01:04:06.645 align:middle line:90%
>> Only two?

01:04:06.645 --> 01:04:07.740 align:middle line:90%
>> Mm-hmm.

01:04:07.740 --> 01:04:11.730 align:middle line:84%
>> Did you search for my
correct name, Andre Luiz?

01:04:11.730 --> 01:04:15.180 align:middle line:84%
>> There are no
mistakes here, sir.

01:04:15.180 --> 01:04:18.240 align:middle line:84%
Now just wait and
the images will show.

01:04:18.240 --> 01:04:19.050 align:middle line:90%
Excuse me.

01:04:19.050 --> 01:04:23.654 align:middle line:90%


01:04:23.654 --> 01:04:25.638 align:middle line:90%
[CHOIR MUSIC]

01:04:25.638 --> 01:05:03.380 align:middle line:90%


01:05:03.380 --> 01:05:11.030 align:middle line:84%
>> Lord, please bless
Doctor Andre Luiz,

01:05:11.030 --> 01:05:12.770 align:middle line:90%
who was so good to me.

01:05:12.770 --> 01:05:15.480 align:middle line:90%


01:05:15.480 --> 01:05:21.701 align:middle line:84%
Let him receive all
the love in this world.

01:05:21.701 --> 01:05:23.990 align:middle line:90%
[SOBBING]

01:05:23.990 --> 01:05:25.025 align:middle line:90%
Bless his family.

01:05:25.025 --> 01:05:27.965 align:middle line:90%


01:05:27.965 --> 01:05:32.540 align:middle line:84%
Our Father in heaven,
hallowed be thy name

01:05:32.540 --> 01:05:35.015 align:middle line:90%
[SOBBING]

01:05:35.015 --> 01:05:43.925 align:middle line:90%


01:05:43.925 --> 01:05:45.420 align:middle line:90%
[HEAVY SIGH]

01:05:45.420 --> 01:05:47.730 align:middle line:84%
>> How long has it been
since you've seen my grandpa?

01:05:47.730 --> 01:05:50.010 align:middle line:84%
>> He's already a
five-year-old boy.

01:05:50.010 --> 01:05:51.930 align:middle line:90%
>> He's someone else?

01:05:51.930 --> 01:05:55.560 align:middle line:84%
>> The same but with a different
body so he can live new

01:05:55.560 --> 01:05:58.170 align:middle line:90%
experiences in the flesh.

01:05:58.170 --> 01:06:01.020 align:middle line:90%
>> I wouldn't stand that.

01:06:01.020 --> 01:06:05.055 align:middle line:84%
>> Sometimes we meet in
our dreams, when he can.

01:06:05.055 --> 01:06:10.370 align:middle line:90%


01:06:10.370 --> 01:06:15.880 align:middle line:84%
My granddaughter, you
will understand one day.

01:06:15.880 --> 01:06:18.790 align:middle line:84%
You will learn how to deal
with the temporary separations

01:06:18.790 --> 01:06:20.270 align:middle line:90%
of life.

01:06:20.270 --> 01:06:25.180 align:middle line:84%
Family ties are forever when
they're built with love.

01:06:25.180 --> 01:06:27.670 align:middle line:84%
Everything that's a
result of vanity and pride

01:06:27.670 --> 01:06:30.790 align:middle line:84%
is lost with the
pain and the journey.

01:06:30.790 --> 01:06:33.158 align:middle line:84%
>> What if I don't
want to understand?

01:06:33.158 --> 01:06:35.200 align:middle line:84%
What if I don't want to
listen to these lectures?

01:06:35.200 --> 01:06:44.790 align:middle line:90%


01:06:44.790 --> 01:06:45.590 align:middle line:90%
I'm sorry.

01:06:45.590 --> 01:06:53.650 align:middle line:90%


01:06:53.650 --> 01:06:56.830 align:middle line:90%
I've missed you so much.

01:06:56.830 --> 01:07:00.034 align:middle line:90%
>> I was looking out for you.

01:07:00.034 --> 01:07:02.524 align:middle line:90%
[BAROQUE MUSIC]

01:07:02.524 --> 01:07:53.920 align:middle line:90%


01:07:53.920 --> 01:07:54.940 align:middle line:90%
>> Dr. Andre.

01:07:54.940 --> 01:07:56.200 align:middle line:90%
[SOBBING]

01:07:56.200 --> 01:07:59.440 align:middle line:90%
Dr. Andre, my husband died.

01:07:59.440 --> 01:08:01.270 align:middle line:90%
And he's not here.

01:08:01.270 --> 01:08:04.180 align:middle line:90%
He hasn't arrived yet.

01:08:04.180 --> 01:08:06.910 align:middle line:90%
Help me rescue him, Dr. Andre.

01:08:06.910 --> 01:08:08.290 align:middle line:90%
Help.

01:08:08.290 --> 01:08:11.395 align:middle line:84%
You're such a good man,
and I need your help.

01:08:11.395 --> 01:08:13.600 align:middle line:90%
Help me, help me.

01:08:13.600 --> 01:08:14.440 align:middle line:90%
[SOBBING]

01:08:14.440 --> 01:08:16.756 align:middle line:90%
>> Miss Amelia, Miss Amelia.

01:08:16.756 --> 01:08:17.748 align:middle line:90%
[SIGH]

01:08:17.748 --> 01:08:20.543 align:middle line:90%
[SOBBING]

01:08:20.543 --> 01:08:23.465 align:middle line:90%
[BAROQUE MUSIC]

01:08:23.465 --> 01:08:28.150 align:middle line:90%


01:08:28.150 --> 01:08:28.950 align:middle line:90%
[CHATTER]

01:08:28.950 --> 01:08:57.502 align:middle line:90%


01:08:57.502 --> 01:09:01.560 align:middle line:84%
>> Andre, the world
needs happy stories.

01:09:01.560 --> 01:09:03.444 align:middle line:90%
>> That's right.

01:09:03.444 --> 01:09:04.440 align:middle line:90%
>> Oh, look.

01:09:04.440 --> 01:09:21.372 align:middle line:90%


01:09:21.372 --> 01:09:24.360 align:middle line:90%
[EXHALES DEEPLY]

